# Low-Load Execution Protocol

The user's machine has limited resources. Do not run heavy commands automatically.

Heavy commands requiring explicit approval:
- npm run build
- npm run lint
- npm test
- npx jest without targeted path
- npx prisma migrate
- npx prisma generate
- broad file scans
- whole-project refactors
- starting multiple dev servers
- indexing or dependency reinstall

Preferred light checks:
- npx tsc --noEmit only when needed and approved
- npx eslint <specific files>
- npx jest <specific test file>
- git diff -- <specific files>
- targeted grep/search
- route-specific manual verification

On Windows/PowerShell, prefer:
$env:NODE_OPTIONS="--max-old-space-size=4096"

If memory problems appear:
- Do not assume code bug.
- Identify whether issue is RAM, stuck process, cache, or actual error.
- Suggest safe cleanup only:
  taskkill /F /IM node.exe
  wsl --shutdown

At task end, report:
- files changed
- commands run
- light/heavy classification
- validation result
- RAM risk
- next lowest-load step

Cloud Agent VMs may run full validation when explicitly tasked for environment setup or release gates.
